Same migration pattern. Note that `vision-apply` writes `ext['surveyor']` *separately* after `createVision` returns ŌĆö this is a second writs-book write outside the cartograph's transaction boundary. So `vision-apply`'s first-apply now produces 1 create event + 1 update event on the writs book (filtered to type === 'vision'). The current test asserts `(create: 1, update: 0)` ŌĆö this will now be `(create: 1, update: 1)` unless vision-apply learns to wrap the cartograph create + surveyor stamp in a single outer `stacks.transaction`.

