Today this works because the body lives on the writs book and the visions book holds only stage/codex. Post-cleanup, *both* live on the writs book ŌĆö a body-only edit (via `clerk.edit`) does mutate the writs book. The assertion semantics shift: filter the watcher to only count events whose `prev.ext?.cartograph` differs from `entry.ext?.cartograph`, or rephrase the test (the cartograph metadata didn't change, even though the writ row did). This is a test rewrite, not a behavioral regression.

